casebody.data:
Devon Jordan TAYLOR
v.
STATE of Maryland No. 25, Sept. Term, 2018 Court of Appeals of Maryland. August 1, 2018
Reconsideration Denied August 23, 2018
Second Motion for Reconsideration Denied October 3, 2018 Submitted by Helki Philipsen, Assistant Public Defender (Paul B. DeWolfe, Public Defender of Maryland of Baltimore, MD) for Petitioner/Cross-Respondent. Submitted by Jessica V. Carter, Assistant Attorney General (Brian E. Frosh, Attorney General of Maryland of Baltimore, MD) for Respondent/Cross-Petitioner. Submitted Before: Barbera, C.J., Greene, Adkins, McDonald, Watts, Hotten, Getty, JJ. PER CURIAM ORDER

The petition for writ of certiorari in the above-entitled case having been granted and thereafter an Unopposed Motion for Clarification and a Joint Motion to Bifurcate Appeal having been filed, it is this 1st day of August, 2018,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the writ of certiorari be, and it is hereby, dismissed with costs, the petition having been improvidently granted.
